<br>
I come from a family that has every generation heed the call to military service. I've participated in every conflict this country has been involved in since 1989. I have earned so many medals(including heroism) and ribbons that if I were to where them all I would like a 3rd world dictator and tend to just wear my warfare device and top three.<br>
<br>
Now after my comments on the day of the attack some people sought to brand me a racist because they could not concieve my perception of whats going to be needed to be done in response to this unwarranted and cowardly attack.<br>
<br>
My anger is not directed towards the greater Arab American community but understand that there are still sleepers in this country that need to be rooted out. <br>
<br>
I have had the Honor and Priviledge to serve beside many outstanding Muslim Americans and Muslim nationals of Nations who are our professed friends. I have lived in many countries thats names end in Stan most notably Uzbekistan(sidenote: I came very very close to marrying the oil ministers daughter but thats a story for my memoirs and she was Muslim.) <br>
